    This is the base class for event dispatcher implementations that forward GWT events to GEWT listeners. This base class implementation already supports mouse events.

      • initEventDispatching

        protected com.google.gwt.event.shared.HandlerRegistration initEventDispatching(com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget rWidget,
                                                                               EventType eEventType)
        This method can be overridden by subclasses to initialize the event dispatching for a certain event type and it's specific widget subclass. The superclass method must alsways be invoked.
        Parameters:
        rWidget - The widget to initialize the event dispatching for
        eEventType - The event type
        Returns:
        The event handler registration or NULL if no handler has been registered

      • setupEventDispatching

        protected void setupEventDispatching(com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget rWidget,
                                     EventType eEventType,
                                     EwtEventHandler rHandler)
        This method performs the setup for the dispatching of a certain event type. It also invokes initEventDispatching(Widget, EventType) which subclasses may implement to perform additional event dispatch initializations-
        Parameters:
        rWidget - The widget to initialize the dispatching for
        eEventType - The event type
        rHandler - The event listener to be notified of events
